radiographic_examinations.findings: Thickened, hyperemic edematous appendix with surrounding fat stranding and peritoneal fascia thickening is consistent with acute appendicitis. There is a small amount of fluid in the pelvis. Otherwise, visualized lung fields, liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, and reproductive organs are within normal limits. Multiple exostosis in both iliac bones, greater on the right, with no evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
